cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about improving the performance of convolutional neural networks through the automation of channel shuffling. As such, it is likely to fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of penalty functions and optimization techniques, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on image data sets, which could also place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
